<TITLE> Govt worried over RMG unrest: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 3 (bdnews24.com)  Commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman on Wednesday expressed concern over disturbances in the readymade garment (RMG) sector in the wake of violent clashes in Gazipur the previous day. Speaking at the launch of a food rationing programme for garment workers, the adviser said: "It's not just the government, but the entire country is proud of our garment industry." "Some recent disturbance in the industry really worried the government," the adviser said. Zillur welcomed any talks over the logical demands of workers. But he vowed to take a tough line on any disorder and violence. Bangladesh Garment Manufacturers and Exporters Association launched the rationing programme in Gazipur on Wednesday. Sixty people were injured Tuesday when police tried to remove a blockade on the Dhaka-Tangail road by angry employees of a Gazipur sweater factory who reacted over the rumoured deaths of 3 fellow workers. bdnews2
